                            <comment id="17154453" author="davidb" created="Thu, 9 Jul 2020 11:35:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The question here is, for the use-case described.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should Feature Model B declare that its part of region r1 (but not export anything into it)?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure about the idea of &apos;inserting&apos; region r1 in feature B because &lt;em&gt;another feature&lt;/em&gt; (feature A) declares it before r2.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17154459" author="cziegeler" created="Thu, 9 Jul 2020 11:44:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think there should be no need to declare an empty region r1 in feature model B. But still, B would get access to r1 through inheritance (r2 inheriting from r1).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
